NOTICE OF MODIFICATIONS (Apache License 2.0, Section 4(b))
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This repository has been modified and substantially extended beyond the
KIRA-Slack base. Notable additions include:

  * AICC — a real-time voice/telephony assistant (streaming voice response)
    with an asynchronous post-call pipeline (recording, transcription,
    classification, notification).
  * Agent Factory — template-based, human-in-the-loop-gated self-extension
    for generating and loading new domain sub-agents at runtime.
  * An MCP server exposing the platform as a tool endpoint, with OAuth 2.1
    (PKCE / DCR) authentication.
  * A redesigned per-session concurrency model ("Session Lane": one worker per
    conversation session, idle self-teardown, and periodic lane cleanup),
    replacing the fixed channel-worker pools of the base.
  * A parallel/sequential sub-agent executor (TaskExecutor) with replanning and
    a shared TaskWorkspace for passing intermediate results between agents.
  * Sub-agent delegation (call_sub_agent), seven domain sub-agents, and
    integrations for eight external services (~219 tools; e.g. CRM with ~111
    tools, Gmail, Google Workspace, ClickUp, telephony).
  * Web and admin dashboards (~18K LOC) for the platform and the AICC console.

Approximately 38K LOC of new code was authored for this repository, in addition
to substantial modifications to the inherited files.

